It is not ignoble for an ambassador to manage the lawsuits of his nationals, because in doing so heis the representative oi his king. The ambassador need not appear in court in person, but may appear by a deputy. The ambassador, like a sovereign, is bound to protect the person and property oi his lellow-countrymen. The laws forbid the governors ol provinces to be involved in disputes ol their own or of others, but the functions of an ambassador, while comparable to those oi a provincial governor in many respects, differ from them in the lact that a Roman provincial governor was amenable to the laws which applied to his lellowsubjects, whereas an ambassador is responsible to his sovereign only.

A Spanish ship in charge of an English Vico-Admiral has been taken by the Dutch. In the case of officials the general presumption is that they have done their duty with diligence and fidelity, but in this instance negligence or even suspicion of complicity is evident.
